				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Bards im the wolrd of Tolken.<a name="43025"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 28 04 11:51 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">I don't know if I'd call tom bombadil a bard, sure he sings songs that are magical, but he's also based on the &quot;green man&quot; legends from early england. He's more of a druid than a bard. His job is to look after the forest afterall. 
<br />
</span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
Tom Bombadil was a bard .. he wasn't looking after the forest so much as after the land and the natural inhabitants of it. He sang and chanted his way through the world. The story of Tom Bombadil is a lyrical poem. His voice was magic ! =) 
<br />

<br />
I would have to  fancy a few  others to be bards too.. the hobbit that sang his way through every encampment and trek... grand hall of kings to the burials of the lords of Rohan. He was a nimble young hobbit with a modest skill at locks and scaling walls, he was quick with a sword but not a full blown warrior. Pippin Oh yes periadoc Brandybuck! All hobbits are bards.. their fashioned after Master Tolkien himself. Samwise made up a bit of song and story now and then and sang to the party to ease their gloom. Their accomplished sneakers with nimble fingers and are light on their feet.. but their not rogues they don't have impressive backstab abilities or any offensive prowess their a naturally peaceful people. 
<br />
Well my two cents on tolkiens bards =) they're everywhere!
<br />
</span></td>
