				<td colspan="2"><span>And dont forget thier bewbies.  In the book, Tolkien describes Galadriels bewbies thusly:
<br />
&quot;Dirty dirty pillows, glistening with dew,
<br />
Golden mounds of pleasure, tipped with rose buds and firm like a stallion's thighs.
<br />
42DD, ahhh the wonders of Eru,
<br />
Secret globes of treasure, hidden in rainment of gold and green, drawing man, elf, dwarf, and hobbit's eyes.&quot;
<br />

<br />
That is just the first stanza in the 12 page epic poem in the &quot;Two towers&quot;, recited by Aragorn, titled &quot;HOOTERS&quot;
<br />
</span></td>
